<TEXT>
as germany ended 45 years of division the 
soviet military chief of staff said the end of the cold war opens 
the road to cooperation between the armed forces of the united 
states and the soviet union 
gen mikhail moiseyev embraced and toasted his american 
counterpart gen colin powell at a dinner reception in new york 
on tuesday on the second day of his first visit to the united 
states 
we have buried the cold war and i dont think that general 
powell or i are going to try to dig it back up moiseyev 51 
told an audience of about 120 us and soviet military officers and 
new york politicians and businessmen 
there are not only wide prospects for friendship between our 
people and the american people but also wide prospects for 
cooperation between our armed forces moiseyev said 
earlier moiseyev commented on the possible use of force against 
iraq by multinational troops stationed in saudi arabia 
he said the economic sanctions against iraq were working and 
that no force should be used in the persian gulf unless it was 
approved by the united nations according to a report in 
wednesdays editions of the new york times 
saddam hussein is finding himself in economic and political 
isolation and he cant survive very long that way moiseyev told 
the newspaper 
but powell who joined moiseyev in the times interview said 
president bush has not ruled out any options in the current crisis 
moiseyev his countrys first deputy minister of defense and 
chief of the general staff is the highestranking soviet military 
officer to visit the united states since soviet marshall sergei 
akhromeyev met with thensecretary of defense frank carlucci in 
december 1987 
powell chairman of the joint chiefs of staff accompanied 
moiseyev from washington where the soviet general arrived monday 
for his sixday visit 
the alliance of our countries lives again in our time under 
the leadership of bush and soviet president mikhail gorbachev 
powell told the audience 
he referred to himself and the soviet general a former 
railroad worker as old soldier powell and old soldier 
moiseyev 
earlier tuesday moiseyev visited fort drum in upstate new york 
and observed the 10th mountain division training drill a battle 
exercise once intended to prepare american soldiers for a military 
encounter with a soviet foe 
the soviet military leader said he had a typical soldiers 
lunch meal and everything was fantastic 
the very soul of what it is to meet the american military was 
what we have accomplished moiseyev said adding that hes a 
little jealous of general powell because hes a man who pays so 
much attention and does so much for the us armed forces 
from new york moiseyev is to travel to other military 
installations in michigan south dakota california and colorado 
in washington moiseyev visited the pentagon and the vietnam 
veterans memorial received a 19gun salute and met with president 
bush 
in our hearts weve felt much more than we have seen in 
meeting the average american citizen we felt care attention 
affection the soviet general said 
