<TEXT>
erich honecker the ousted and reviled 
leader of the vanished east germany spent reunification night 
behind the walls of the soviet military hospital where he is 
confined 
like the other 166 million citizens of the now extinct state he 
ruled for 18 years the excommunist party chief became a citizen 
of united democratic germany at the stroke of midnight tuesday 
residents of beelitz 20 miles south of berlin had decorated 
buildings with german flags for the occassion and mass was 
celebrated in the town church 
the 77yearold honecker who withdrew in seclusion and disgrace 
after he was ousted a year ago amid massive prodemocracy protests 
can sometimes be seen strolling through the pine and birch forest 
on the hospital grounds 
you can see him at night walking around quietly its a very 
restful place said a soviet civilian taking a walk along the 
road next to the hospital the soviet did not give his name and 
said he was receiving treatment for an eye ailment at the facility 
the hospital and oldfashioned brick villas on the grounds are 
surrounded by a thick white wall 
honecker directed the building of the 1961 berlin wall that kept 
east germans trapped in the communist state for 28 years 
most of them detested honecker 
asked once what he liked most about unity wolf biermann the 
former east german dissident expelled to west germany in the 1970s 
replied that honecker became a citizen of united germany and 
cant do anything about it 
honecker was accused of corruption and expelled from the 
communist party in december but was spared the indignity of 
imprisonment when doctors determined that he suffered from a kidney 
tumor and was too ill to survive jail life 
he was transferred to the soviet military hospital earlier this 
year soviet officers at the gate declined to allow a western 
reporter on the grounds 
unity is the business of the germans we wont interfere 
said one he said the base had no plans to celebrate unification 
the 360000 soviet troops in what was east germany are scheduled 
to return home by 1994 
honecker could face trial and imprisonment in the united 
germany where he is under criminal investigation for allegedly 
giving shoottokill orders to border guards and harboring leftist 
terrorists wanted in west germany 
