and kuwait new but undefined arrangements for stability in the 
persian gulf and a settlement between the arabs and israel 
later bush told reporters there is no flexibility here 
he said his policy had not changed and they should not look for 
nuances hidden meanings in his speech 
and yet mixed in with the denunciation of saddam hussein and 
even the threat of a war crimes trial the president offered more 
in the way of a diplomatic alternative than at any point in the 
twomonth crisis 
in effect bush said withdraw then negotiate implicit is an 
opportunity for saddam to take up his territorial demands with the 
ousted rulers of kuwait provided they are restored to power 
the iraqi leader feeling the pressure of an international trade 
cutoff has complained that iraq is being singled out while other 
countries actions are not checked by the united nations 
saddam has pointed an accusing finger at israel seeking to 
swing other arabs to his side by projecting iraq as the bearer of 
the banner for an israeli withdrawal from the west bank and gaza 
which jordan and syria lost in the 1967 mideast war 
but at least one major arab nation egypt reportedly took 
exception to any gesture to the iraqi leader 
butros ghali the egyptian minister of state for foreign 
affairs discussed bushs speech with david levy the israeli 
foreign minister afterward diplomatic sources reported that ghali 
said saddam should not be given any chance to claim a bonus for 
his takeover of kuwait and that the arabisraeli dispute should not 
be linked to it 
just as bush took a cue from soviet foreign minister eduard a 
shevardnadze in raising the spectre of a war crimes trial for 
saddam the president followed the lead of french president 
francois mitterrand in offering saddam a way to avert 
confrontation 
mitterrands fourstep proposal before the un general assembly 
last week also held out to saddam the potential of an arabisraeli 
settlement if iraq gives up kuwait 
senior us officials who had dismissed any linking of the two 
disputes showed little interest in the french proposal at the 
time 
but on sunday the birthday of the muslim prophet mohammed 
saddam said iraq was prepared for a dialogue with france so that 
everything is based on clear ideas and actions 
mitterrand said one of his objectives was to ensure israels 
security bush of course would do nothing less for americas best 
friend in the middle east 
and yet saddam and other arab leaders also are aware that us 
policy seeks israeli withdrawal from the west bank and the golan 
heights 
bushs script for the area in the event of an iraqi withdrawal 
holds promise of realizing that goal 
whether it entices saddam to execute a complete turnabout only 
the iraqi leader can say 
the president is providing a way out short of war for saddam 
and yet he also is prepared to take the ultimate military step if 
scorned 
there are 165000 us troops in the persian gulf region and 
more arriving daily 
brent scowcroft the presidents assistant for national security 
affairs and other senior officials have been warning that us 
patience is running out 
were still giving sanctions the time to work the time to be 
effective bush told reporters monday and im a little 
encouraged that perhaps they are having a strong effect 
the choice evidently is saddam husseins 
 
editors note barry schweid is the associated press chief 
diplomatic writer 
