more than 300 yards away before a third shot from closer range 
prompted the freighter to halt officials said 
a french search party then boarded the freighter officials 
said the vessel was allowed to resume its passage after searchers 
determined it did not appear to be violating the un embargo 
imposed on iraq and occupied kuwait 
the incident occurred in the bab al mandab strait linking the 
red sea and the gulf of aden french officials did not say where 
the freighter began its journey or where it was headed 
it was the fifth interception in which warning shots were fired 
since the blockade was imposed aug 6 four days after iraq invaded 
kuwait the earlier incidents involved us warships and an 
australian frigate 
