nasa completed final preparations 
tuesday for the countdown of space shuttle discovery due to lift 
off this week with five astronauts and a plutoniumpowered sun 
probe 
the countdown clock was to start ticking at 330 am wednesday 
liftoff is scheduled for saturday morning 
a generator containing 237 pounds of plutonium238 was 
installed tuesday in the satellite tucked inside discoverys cargo 
bay the satellite called ulysses will use electricity generated 
from the decaying plutonium during its fiveyear journey in space 
technicians also repaired a broken wire in discoverys engine 
compartment that was preventing a liquid oxygen valve from opening 
environmental activists opposed to nasas use of plutonium have 
gone to court in an attempt to halt the launch a hearing is 
scheduled for thursday in washington dc before us district 
oliver gasch who refused to stop atlantis from lifting off last 
year with a plutoniumpowered satellite bound for jupiter 
the activists fear a challengerlike accident would scatter the 
deadly plutonium over florida and result in untold cancer 
fatalities they say nasas inability to fix the shuttle columbias 
hydrogen leaks calls into question the space agencys competency 
nasa tried four times in four months to launch columbia before 
stopping two weeks ago to turn its attention to discovery columbia 
is expected to remain grounded until late this year or early next 
year 
a newly repaired atlantis grounded by hydrogen leaks in june 
is scheduled to carry a secret military satellite into orbit in 
early november 
nasa officials insist the chances of plutonium being released 
into the atmosphere are extremely small and would pose little 
health risk even if it did there is no other way to get ulysses 
into an unprecedented orbit over the suns poles they said 
weve done everything we can to ensure safety said willis 
meeks nasas project manager for ulysses were ready and im 
optimistic were going to launch on the 6th 
after being released from discovery ulysses is to speed toward 
jupiter and use the giant planets gravity to be whipped into the 
proper solar orbit if discovery does not lift off by oct 23 the 
750 million mission will have to wait until late 1991 for the 
proper planetary alignment 
the fourday mission would be nasas first shuttle flight in 
nearly half a year discovery was the last spaceship to be 
launched its cargo was the hubble space telescope which later was 
found to have a flawed mirror 
