sent some people in search of shelters while others made worried 
phone calls to authorities they were told the sirens went off by 
accident 
israelis woke up to a barrage of radio talk shows and newspaper 
articles on how to deal with the masks 
to those who wondered whether iraqi president saddam husseins 
threat was serious the reply from the experts was iraq probably 
will not attack israel but its best to be ready 
most callers to israel radio focused on what people should do 
with the sealed box containing a mask and syringe with a nerve gas 
antidote the answer was keep it in the closet away from the 
kids and dont open it except when ordered 
how they asked can we be sure the masks will work what about 
asthma sufferers and babies how does one protect the rest of the 
body 
in principle the gas only causes damage when it is breathed 
in through the lungs it should not hurt the skin said col 
david klivansky answering a question on israel radio 
klivansky added that in the sealed rooms that israelis have 
already been told to prepare for a possible gas attack you need 
only the mask 
the kits will be distributed at schools and notices mailed to 
citizens telling them where to pick them up 
yitzhak samuel who lives in the tel aviv suburb of ramat 
hasharon said his family already had received masks and felt safe 
we have them high up in the closet far from the kids he 
said on army radio we received lectures on a video and we are 
not afraid 
the daily yediot ahronot devoted three pages to the gas masks a 
picture showed a young woman demonstrating their use in the manner 
of an airline stewardess other photos showed protective tents for 
infants and special childrens masks 
a cartoon depicted israeli prime minister yitzhak shamir 
unwrapping a gas mask and advising a menacinglooking saddam 
dont panic 
one concern voiced by israeli officials has been that a decision 
to distribute gas masks might be read by saddam as a warlike move 
another fear is that it will scare the israeli public 
we can expect the public to behave in an adult manner now 
although the announcement about distribution in our view will 
raise the level of anxiety reserve brig gen aharon vardi a 
civil defense official said on israel television 
indeed signs of nervousness already are apparent 
in the past weeks while officials debated how to prepare for a 
chemical attack people rushed to buy sealing tape for their rooms 
and baking soda for homemade gas masks 
still officials are trying to make the gas masks a part of 
everyday life just like the constant appeals to be alert for 
suspicious packages that could be bombs 
as army spokesman brig gen nachman shai put it the public 
should accept the gas masks simply as another way of living in 
the holy land 
