<TEXT>
the battle scars on the reichstag testify to 
germanys turbulent past and the old parliament buildings place in 
german history 
with the hoisting of germanys flag and the singing of the 
national anthem in front of the reichstag at midnight tuesday the 
old parliament building becomes the focal point of unification 
ceremonies 
on thursday the reichstag will be host to the first session of 
german lawmakers in nearly six decades as legislators from the west 
and east come together for the first time in the new united 
germany 
the sandstone edifice was heavily damaged in the last days of 
world war ii as german troops and soviet soldiers engaged in fierce 
fighting for the capital 
after handtohand combat red army soldiers raised a red soviet 
flag atop the reichstag in a famous world war ii photograph that 
symbolized the crushing of adolf hitlers third reich 
after the war the west german parliament met occasionally at 
the reichstag but never convened in full restoration of the 
building was completed in 1971 but the main hall where thursdays 
session will be held was deliberately left empty as a reminder of 
the unresolved german question 
germany got its first parliament in 1871 after kaiser wilhelm i 
unified the country and berlin became the capital the building and 
the parliament were called reichstag meaning imperial legislature 
the present reichstag building was completed in 1894 after 10 
years of construction 
a mysterious fire on feb 27 1933 just a month after hitler 
became chancellor gutted the building 
the blaze served as hitlers pretext to force passage of an act 
that allowed his government to make laws without reichstag 
approval 
the inscription dem deutschen volke to the german people 
was added to the building during world war i and is still visible 
over the main portal 
