29day walkout threatened the nations most precious commodity 
education 
union leaders appealed the ruling to state commonwealth court 
common pleas judge samuel lehrer said the strike by members of 
the temple association of university professionals damaged the 
education of some 29000 students and also harmed the public the 
walkout began sept 4 the first day of classes 
education is vital to the health safety and welfare of this 
nation and this community said lehrer who ordered the faculty 
to return wednesday 
temple had threatened to cancel 1900 of its 4700 classes that 
havent met since the strike began leaving 6000 students without 
any classes and 23000 others minus one or more classes union 
officials estimated that about 600 members joined the strike 
the union which represents 1100 teachers librarians and other 
academic professionals were meeting tuesday afternoon to decide 
whether to defy the order 
