when they blocked traffic on a busy street to protest rules they 
say unfairly deny disability benefits to many women infected with 
the aids virus 
the aids activists said the social security administration in 
determining eligibility for disability benefits is ignoring many 
of the diseases and infections that are common in women infected 
with the virus 
the result is that many women with disabling conditions 
including gynecological disorders like pelvic inflammatory disease 
and chronic vaginal infections are denied benefits the protesters 
said 
these disorders are not on a list of infections and diseases 
used by the centers for disease control to define aids much of the 
list was compiled in the early days of the epidemic when most aids 
victims were white middleclass homosexual men 
but this definition misses the ailments and conditions common to 
women infected with the human immunodeficiency virus or hiv which 
causes aids the activists said 
its time they stopped denying women said phyllis sharpe 
39 of new york who marched in the demonstration led by the aids 
