the senate on tuesday overwhelmingly approved 
a resolution praising president bushs actions in the persian gulf 
and supporting continued deployment of us troops to deter iraqi 
aggression 
but the debate leading up to the 963 vote had nervous echoes of 
25 years ago when a similar act opened the way to escalation of 
the vietnam war 
senator after senator rose to say bush could not use the 
resolution as justification for future military moves in fact 
debate seemed aimed more at stating what the document was not than 
what it was 
this resolution is not an authorization for the use of force 
now or in the future said senate majority leader george 
