federation said the fronts recruiters aim mainly at students aged 
15 to 17 because according to the law they are juveniles and 
their legal responsibility is limited 
acting education minister raul allard said his office will 
launch a campaign of orientation to counter the fronts 
recruiting efforts in the schools 
explained claudio orrego president of the santiago catholic 
university students federation we must make young people to 
understand that violence is not democratic or heroic they must 
understand that the country is no longer under a dictatorship 
the lautaro front was organized in the mid1980s to fight the 
military regime of gen augusto pinochet to the chagrin of the 
elected civilian government it has remained active after pinochet 
was succeeded in march by president patricio aylwin 
the goverment change did not impress the front which has vowed 
to continue its struggle calling aylwin a bourgeois enemy 
another guerrilla group created to fight the pinochet regime 
the manuel rodriguez patriotic front has virtually ceased 
operations as a result of the new political situation in chile 
