the federal reserve will cut interest rates in 
support of the deficitreduction package but the amount of the 
decline is likely to disappoint the bush administration and not be 
enough to keep the country out of a recession private economists 
predict 
these analysts said rising inflationary pressures from a 
doubling of oil prices will severely limit the feds maneuvering 
room despite administration contentions that interest rates need to 
fall swiftly in order to stave off an economic slump 
the feds top policymakers gathered in washington today for a 
key meeting of the federal open market committee or fomc the 
panel composed of fed board members in washington and fed regional 
presidents meets eight times a year to map the course of interest 
rates 
while the results of the closeddoor deliberations are not 
released for six weeks many economists said they expected a vote 
by the fomc to nudge shortterm interest rates down by onefourth 
of a percentage point 
