in uneventful us trading tuesday after moving mostly higher 
overseas 
gold prices skidded on european and asian markets but gold 
gained modestly in the united states as the previous days selloff 
here subsidied 
currency dealers could not put their fingers on precisely why 
the dollar weakened in the united states but they said trading 
volume was light indicating sellers lacked conviction 
a widespread belief that us interest rates eventually will 
move lower as the economy struggles to stay out of a recession was 
offered as a possible reason for the diminished demand for dollars 
lower us interest rates would make returns on 
dollardenominated holdings less appealing and could steer money 
into higheryielding foreign investments 
the chances that us rates will fall have risen since white 
house and congressional negotiators reached agreement on a fiscal 
1991 budget 
