<TEXT>
apple computer inc plans to offer 
cheaper versions of its macintosh machine as part of a strategy to 
win market share that chairman john sculley hopes will help the 
company withstand a recession 
the plan begins with three new macintosh computers to be 
introduced oct 15 accompanied by a 40 million advertising 
campaign 
the macintosh classic comparable to the popular 2569 se 
model will carry a list price of about 1000 and a street price 
as low as 700 to 800 according to sources close to apple 
the other two models available with color monitors will be 
listed at about 3000 and 5000 or several thousand dollars less 
than comparable macintoshes in the current line 
the basic strategy is to go after a larger share of the 
market sculley said at a preview of the campaign we have no 
sacred cows as far as pricing this means that this will be the 
most aggressive pricing that apple has ever had 
in a weak economy as the united states certainly is in its 
a lot more reassuring to be introducing three major products at 
price points that are going to be extremely affordable 
critics of apple have long complained that its macintosh line 
which ranges from 1799 for the macplus to 11000 for the fx is 
too expensive apples gross margins on those products is about 50 
percent one of the highest in the industry sculley said 
as a result apple has racked up profits but stagnated with only 
about 9 percent of the desktop computer market inexpensive 
clones of international business machines corp personal 
computers have dominated the low end of the market 
the windows software program from microsoft which gives ibm 
computers the look and feel of the macintosh also has forced 
apple to examine how it can distinguish itself 
for us to be really successful in the 1990s we want to have 
much more than a 9 percent share sculley said he declined to say 
what share of the market he is aiming for or what gross margins 
hell be satisfied with 
apple which does nearly half of its business outside the united 
states is introducing its new computers simultaneously in 121 
countries the company expects the computers to be a hit especially 
in japan where apples business has been doubling annually 
part of our business has been extremely strong sculley 
said weve continued to gain market share with our 
highperformance modular macs in business while we clearly had 
some need for freshening up at the low end of our product line the 
high end is very resilient and strong 
apple will adjust its prices throughout its macintosh line but 
it is not abandoning its top models 
i want to make sure this isnt seen as a flipflop as if 
were now only in lowend systems said michael spindler apples 
chief operating officer we dont want to divest from markets we 
want to invest to make this a much broader growth business for 
apple 
he said the company will pull all the stops out go a little 
bit overboard in manufacturing the new machines in anticipation 
of strong demand 
if you have a brand new product in which you believe it 
doesnt make sense to run it tight spindler said 
sculley said the new products and new strategy are among the 
most important events in his eight years with the company 
he said apple is also working on several notebooksize 
computers 
miniaturization is one of the major themes were focusing on 
in research and development he said i think thats going to 
be extremely important in the 1990s 
sculley acknowledged criticsim that apple has failed to come up 
with a lightweight portable the portable mac is a bulky heavy 
machine that seems almost antiquated compared to competitive 
models 
while apple has started late in some of these areas we can do 
a lot more than just catch up sculley said we see this as a 
chance to get real differentiation in the 1990s 
he said miniaturization is evident in the new desktop models 
that apple will show off 
it means extremely high reliability because we have fewer 
components on the board he said the reliability of the new 
products we think is going to be significantly higher than anything 
thats been brought out 
were basically saying this is the year of the new customer 
and we are reaching out to people who have never experienced apple 
before many of those people dont know an awful lot about personal 
computers and we want their first experience to be extremely 
satisfying so the product reliability is important 
